[/asy]

The height of the pole is 15 m and Paul is 3 m above the ground, so the height of the triangle is 15 m - 3 m = 12 m. The base of the triangle is 5 m. Using the Pythagorean theorem, the length of the hypotenuse, which is the section of the rope to the left of Paul, is:

$\sqrt{\text{base}^2 + \text{height}^2} = \sqrt{5^2 + 12^2} = \sqrt{25 + 144} = \sqrt{169} = 13\text{ m}$.

Now let's consider the right section of the rope.

[asy]
draw((5,0)--(14,0)--(14,15)--(5,3)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
draw((5,0)--(6,0)--(6,1)--(5,1)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
