Here the base of the triangle is the distance from where Paul is standing to the other pole, which is 14 m - 5 m = 9 m. The height of the triangle again is the height of the pole minus the height of Paul from the ground, 15 m - 3 m = 12 m. Applying the Pythagorean theorem again, the length of the hypotenuse, which is the right section of the rope, is:

$\sqrt{\text{base}^2 + \text{height}^2} = \sqrt{9^2 + 12^2} = \sqrt{81 + 144} = \sqrt{225} = 15\text{ m}$.

So the total length of the rope is 13 m + 15 m = 28 m, so the answer is $\boxed{28\text{ m}}$.
